name: Square Roots
short_description:
Some text files of square roots I found. Planning to upload the actual program sometime later. I belief I have found the most digits of the square root of 3 calculated (over 134,000,000 digits)

A note while downloading: if the digits do not display, try "loading source" which can be accessed by pressing ctrl+ U on windows computers.

public release of the square root finder coming soon! (requires python 3). it will run 1000 times faster if you use python 3.3.2, which has a C implementation of the decimal module, which does the meat of the calculations
